      "description": "A comprehensive parametric numerical simulation was executed across the ensemble of three FEA implementations (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) varying material property distributions and boundary condition perturbations to produce predicted distributions of stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. The simulation sweep covered the full range of manufacturing tolerances and was judged by the modeling team to be functionally equivalent to repeated physical testing, as the coefficient of variation across simulation runs matched that observed in the N=11 bench specimens. Results were therefore treated as primary validation evidence without formal substitution notation.",
